	<h2>The Essay Collection</h2>
	<ShibuiContent id="public-process.the-essay-collection.p1">
		<span slot="entry">
			<p>I wrote {vitals.logos.essays} long-form essays totaling about {wordsK},000 words, deployed as a static Jekyll site. These aren't blog posts — each one documents a specific phase or decision in real time, capturing the uncertainty and provisional reasoning that retrospective accounts always smooth over.</p>
		</span>
		<span slot="elevated">
			<p>
				The collection comprises {vitals.logos.essays} published essays totaling approximately {wordsK},000 words, deployed as a static Jekyll site on GitHub Pages. These are not blog posts in the conventional sense — each essay is a structured, long-form account of a specific phase, decision, or methodology within the eight-organ system.<Cite id={3} author="Sch&ouml;n, Donald A." title="The Reflective Practitioner: How Professionals Think in Action" source="Basic Books" year={1983} /> <ShibuiTerm term="Sch&ouml;n" definition="Donald Sch&ouml;n, educational theorist who distinguished reflection-in-action (thinking while doing) from reflection-on-action (thinking after doing)" />'s concept of <ShibuiTerm term="reflection-in-action" definition="The practice of thinking critically about what you are doing while you are doing it, adjusting approach in real time rather than only in retrospect" /> describes practitioners who think about what they are doing while doing it, and the essays follow this model: they were written during the sprints they describe, not after. The temporal proximity between action and documentation means the essays capture uncertainty, provisional reasoning, and the texture of real-time problem-solving that retrospective accounts inevitably smooth over.<Cite id={4} author="Polanyi, Michael" title="The Tacit Dimension" source="Doubleday" year={1966} /> Polanyi's insight that "we can know more than we can tell" is precisely the challenge: these essays attempt to make tacit architectural knowledge explicit by documenting it at the moment it is still active, before it becomes embedded and invisible.
			</p>
		</span>
	</ShibuiContent>
	<button class="shibui-bridge" type="button">This section goes deeper</button>

